#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:1
msgid "Newsletter"
msgstr "Boletín informativo (Newsletter)"

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:3
msgid "Our newsletter, Carpentry Clippings, appears every two weeks."
msgstr "Nuestro Newsletter, Carpentry Clippings, aparece cada dos semanas."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:5
msgid "Newsletter content"
msgstr "Contenido del Newsletter"

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:7
msgid ""
"Highlights from the Carpentries Community Calendar: Includes items from The "
"Carpentries calendar, such as upcoming events."
msgstr ""
"Aspectos destacados del calendario (Community Calendar) de The Carpentries: "
"Incluye elementos del calendario de The Carpentries, como los próximos "
"eventos."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:8
msgid ""
"Community News: A place to report on all kinds of things - events, workshop "
"or conference reports, awards, lesson releases, new reports ..."
msgstr ""
"Noticias de la comunidad (Community News): Un lugar para informar sobre todo"
" tipo de cosas: eventos, informes de talleres o conferencias, premios, "
"lanzamientos de lecciones, nuevos informes ..."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:9
msgid ""
"Committee and Task Force Activity: Includes announcements directly from task"
" force and committee chairs and summaries from meeting notes."
msgstr ""
"Actividades del comité y grupo de trabajo: Incluye anuncios directamente del"
" grupo de trabajo y presidentes de comité, y resúmenes de las notas de la "
"reunión."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:10
msgid ""
"What you may have missed on the blog and mailing lists: Includes highlights "
"of key conversations on the Discuss email list, other lists or things on the"
" blog that need further highlighting."
msgstr ""
"Si no lo viste en el blog o en el email: incluye los aspectos más destacados"
" de las conversaciones en las listas de correo electrónico, Discuss u otras "
"listas, o cosas del blog que deben resaltarse."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:11
msgid ""
"Tweet of the Week: One noteworthy tweet is chosen and a screen captured "
"image is included."
msgstr ""
"Tweet de la semana: se elige un tweet destacado junto a una captura de "
"pantalla."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:12
msgid ""
"Optional: Papers & manuscripts for and from the community: Includes "
"announcements that were made on the Discuss email list, Twitter, or other "
"media."
msgstr ""
"Opcional: Artículos y manuscritos para y desde la comunidad: Incluye "
"anuncios que se hicieron en la lista de correo electrónico Discuss, Twitter "
"u otros medios."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:13
msgid ""
"Optional: Offcuts: Includes other unusual news that may be of interest."
msgstr ""
"Opcional: Offcuts: incluye otras noticias inusuales que pueden ser de "
"interés."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:14
msgid ""
"Optional: Joinery: Includes other ways to get involved in the Carpentries "
"community and ways the Carpentries community is involved in other "
"conferences, etc."
msgstr ""
"Opcional: Joinery: incluye otras formas de involucrarse en la comunidad de "
"The Carpentries y formas en que la comunidad de The Carpentries participa en"
" otras conferencias, etc."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:15
msgid ""
"Optional: Toolshed (Posts from our Past): A place to highlight handy posts "
"from the blog or discussion list archives that might still be relevant to "
"postings to lists and other issues."
msgstr ""
"Opcional: Toolshed (publicaciones de nuestro pasado): un lugar para resaltar"
" publicaciones de utilidad que vienen del blog o de las listas de discusión "
"que aún podrían ser relevantes para publicaciones en listas y otras "
"ediciones."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:16
msgid ""
"Community Job postings: Includes information that has come through on the "
"Discuss email list, Twitter, and other media."
msgstr ""
"Ofertas de empleo en la comunidad: incluye información que se ha publicado "
"en la lista de correo electrónico Discuss, en Twitter y otros medios."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:17
msgid ""
"Other places to connect: This section is standardized for all newsletter "
"issues."
msgstr ""
"Otros lugares de contacto: esta sección está estandarizada para todas las "
"ediciones del boletín."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:19
msgid "Submitting newsletter content"
msgstr "Someter contenido al Newsletter"

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:21
msgid ""
"Carpentries staff manage newsletter content through this private Asana "
"project.  Submissions from community members are welcome by emailing "
"newsletter@carpentries.org."
msgstr ""
"El personal de The Carpentries administra el Newsletter a través de este "
"proyecto privado de Asana. Los contenidos sometidos por los miembros de la "
"comunidad son bienvenidos enviando un correo electrónico a "
"newsletter@carpentries.org."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:23
msgid "Publishing the newsletter"
msgstr "Publicación del Newsletter"

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:25
msgid ""
"This information is intended for staff or community members who have taken "
"on the responsibility of publishing the newsletter."
msgstr ""
"Esta información está destinada al personal o miembros de la comunidad que "
"han asumido la responsabilidad de publicar el Newsletter."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:27
msgid "Each newsletter is a campaign on MailChimp."
msgstr "Cada Newsletter es una campaña en MailChimp"

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:29
msgid ""
"To create a new newsletter, log in to MailChimp and click on Campaigns.  "
"Make a copy of the latest newsletter and rename the copy to reflect the "
"current date (e.g. Carpentry Clippings, 27 March, 2018.)."
msgstr ""
"Para crear un Newsletter, inicie sesión en MailChimp y haga clic en "
"Campaigns. Haga una copia del último boletín y cambie el nombre de la copia "
"para reflejar la fecha actual (por ejemplo, Carpentry Clippings, 27 de marzo"
" de 2018)."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:31
msgid ""
"Check the To field is correctly set as going to x number of newsletter "
"subscribers."
msgstr ""
"Verifique que el campo Para (To) esté configurado correctamente ya que va a "
"x suscriptores del Newsletter."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:33
msgid "Check the From field is correctly set as coming from The Carpentries."
msgstr ""
"Verifique que el campo De (From) esté configurado correctamente como "
"proveniente de The Carpentries."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:35
msgid ""
"Make sure the date in the Subject line is changed to the new newsletter "
"date."
msgstr ""
"Asegúrese de que la fecha en la línea Asunto (Subject) se cambie a la nueva "
"fecha del Newsletter."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:37
msgid ""
"Select Edit design to add newsletter content. When the newsletter opens, "
"click the pencil icon in the newsletter on the left to open the newsletter "
"for editing. (Editing is all done within the right pane; the left pane "
"renders the public view as you edit.)"
msgstr ""
"Seleccione editar diseño para agregar contenido al newsletter. Cuando abra "
"el newsletter, haga clic en el ícono del lápiz en el Newsletter de la "
"izquierda para abrirlo y editarlo. (La edición se realiza dentro del panel "
"derecho; el panel izquierdo muestra la vista pública a medida que se edita)."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:39
msgid ""
"Remove the old content and paste in the new, leaving the headings so that "
"the formatting for them is not disturbed."
msgstr ""
"Elimine el contenido anterior y péguelo en el nuevo, dejando los encabezados"
" para que el formato no se vea afectado."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:41
msgid "Be sure to update the date at the top of the email as well."
msgstr ""
"Asegúrese de actualizar la fecha en la parte superior del correo electrónico"
" también."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:43
msgid ""
"Highlight each paragraph and click Clear styles if anything you are copying "
"in appears in bold when you don't want it to."
msgstr ""
"Resalte cada párrafo y haga clic en Borrar estilos si todo lo que está "
"copiando aparece en negrita cuando no lo desee."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:45
msgid ""
"Add images by clicking on the Image icon in the edit window.  All images "
"must be no more than 550px wide to render properly. These can be resized "
"within MailChimp by working with the image styling and location."
msgstr ""
"Agregue imágenes haciendo clic en el ícono Imagen en la ventana de edición. "
"Las imágenes deben tener menos de 550 px de ancho para renderizarse "
"correctamente. Se pueden redimensionar dentro de MailChimp trabajando con el"
" estilo de imagen (image styling) y la ubicación de la imagen."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:47
msgid ""
"Go to Preview and Test to preview the newsletter before sending it out. This"
" includes a desktop and mobile version preview.  Send a test email to "
"yourself to preview it in your email client."
msgstr ""
"Vaya a Vista previa y prueba (Preview and Test) para obtener una vista "
"previa del Newsletter antes de enviarlo. Esto incluye una vista previa de la"
" versión de escritorio y móvil. Envíe un correo electrónico de prueba para "
"obtener una vista previa en su cliente de correo electrónico."

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:49
msgid ""
"Save and Close and schedule the newsletter to be sent.  This should be set "
"for Wednesday at 9 am Eastern time. Be sure it is set for AM, not PM. A "
"confirmation message saying \"Rock On! Your campaign has been scheduled\" "
"will be displayed, and a link to a published view of the newsletter will be "
"displayed. Paste this link into the staff channel so staff have a chance to "
"review the newsletter before it goes out."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:51
msgid ""
"The newsletter will now be locked. If any changes need to be made after ther"
" newsletter has been scheduled, you will need to pause the campaign, make "
"changes, and restart the campaign."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:53
msgid ""
"After a campaign has been paused and then restarted, it is important to "
"doublecheck that the date and time for sending out the newsletter is still "
"correctly set as this will often default to the current time, rather than "
"the original scheduled time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/communications/newsletter.md:55
msgid ""
"As soon as the newsletter has been sent out, move it to the Carpentry "
"Clippings folder. This adds it to the searchable online archive findable "
"through our website. To move it, check the box next to the newsletter and "
"select the Carpentry Clippings folder when the Move to option appears."
msgstr ""

